            <title>[HBASE-303] [hbase] Startup scripts should wait until hdfs as cleared &apos;safe mode&apos; </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-303</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the underying hdfs is in &apos;safe mode&apos;, hbase gets confused.  hbase start scripts should just wait on hdfs leaving &apos;safe mode&apos; &amp;#8211; perhaps emitting a status message &amp;#8211; before proceeding with cluster startup.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
